## Next Steps for Deployment
To enable Web Analytics on Vercel:
1. Deploy the project to Vercel
2. Navigate to your project's Analytics section in the Vercel dashboard
3. Click the "Enable" button to activate Web Analytics
4. Analytics will start collecting data after the next deployment

## Technical Notes
- The Analytics component is self-contained and requires no additional configuration
- It will automatically track page views and web vitals
- The component is lightweight and won't impact application performance
- In development mode, analytics data is not sent to Vercel
- After deployment, verify by checking the browser's Network tab for requests to `/_vercel/insights/*`

## Implementation Details
The Analytics component placement in App.js ensures:
- It's rendered on all routes (placed outside the Routes component)
- It initializes once when the app loads
- It has access to the React Router context for proper page tracking
- It follows React best practices for analytics integration
